        "body" : "So `trap function EXIT` means \"execute function on receiving the EXIT signal\", which includes normal exit and errors. (I'm not sure what it does on `exec` ðŸ¤”) `trap - EXIT` means \"clear the handler for the EXIT signal\".\r\n\r\nThis works for trapping real signals too (`EXIT` is kind of a special, synthetic signal Bash adds), but I've not really found a use for that yet. Trapping `EXIT`, however, is really useful in lots of situations.",
